data.name: Grilled Chicken Tacos with Avocado Crema
data.quickTastyDescription: Delicious grilled chicken tacos topped with a creamy avocado sauce, perfect for a quick and satisfying meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: Preheat the grill to medium-high heat.
Season the chicken breasts with taco seasoning and grill for about 6-7 minutes on each side or until fully cooked.
While the chicken is grilling, prepare the avocado crema by blending together ripe avocados, sour cream, lime juice, and cilantro until smooth.
Remove the chicken from the grill and let it rest for a few minutes before slicing it into strips.
Warm the corn tortillas on the grill for about 30 seconds on each side.
Assemble the tacos by placing grilled chicken on the tortillas and topping with avocado crema, cherry tomatoes, and shredded lettuce.
